                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Data model</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>The base of a <trademark>jACOB</trademark> application design is the data model.
                        The data model itself consists of:</para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem><para>tables,</para></listitem>
                            <listitem><para><glossterm linkend="tableAlias">table aliases</glossterm>,</para></listitem>
                            <listitem><para>relations and <glossterm linkend="relationSet">relation sets</glossterm>,</para></listitem>
                            <listitem><para><glossterm linkend="browser">browsers</glossterm> and</para></listitem>
                            <listitem><para><glossterm linkend="tableHooks">table hooks</glossterm>.</para></listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                        
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Creation of a data model</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
